---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import TestimonialStrip from '../components/sections/TestimonialStrip.astro';
import Icon from '../components/ui/Icon.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
import { breadcrumbSchema, combineSchema } from '../utils/seo';

const crumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'About', href: '/about' },
];

const philosophy = [
  {
    icon: 'book-open',
    title: 'Education first',
    text: 'Nobody should sign a thirty-year obligation they do not understand. Before you commit to anything, you will know what your payment is made of, what each option costs, and why I am recommending one over another. If you cannot explain your loan to your spouse, I have not finished my job.',
  },
  {
    icon: 'compass',
    title: 'Creative structuring',
    text: 'A denial is almost always a program mismatch, not a verdict. Bank statement, 1099, P&L, asset depletion, DSCR, non-contingent purchase, first-lien HELOC — knowing which tool fits which situation is the skill that took twenty years to build, and it is the entire value I bring.',
  },
  {
    icon: 'heart',
    title: 'Advisor for life',
    text: 'A mortgage is a transaction. A mortgage advisor is a relationship. I want the call when rates move, when you are thinking about a rental property, when your kid is buying their first house. That standard changes how I handle every file, because I expect to still be your lender in fifteen years.',
  },
];

const clients = [
  { icon: 'graduation-cap', title: 'First-time buyers', text: 'Guided from budget to keys with every step explained before it happens.' },
  { icon: 'arrow-up-right', title: 'Move-up buyers', text: 'Non-contingent offers so you buy the next home without selling first.' },
  { icon: 'briefcase', title: 'Self-employed owners', text: 'Bank statement, 1099, P&L, and no-ratio programs built for how you actually earn.' },
  { icon: 'shield-check', title: 'Veterans', text: 'Full entitlement, funding fee exemptions, and every benefit you earned.' },
  { icon: 'stethoscope', title: 'Physicians', text: 'Programs that account for residency income, student debt, and a signed contract.' },
  { icon: 'trending-up', title: 'Real estate investors', text: 'DSCR financing, LLC vesting, and portfolio scaling past conventional limits.' },
  { icon: 'gem', title: 'Luxury buyers', text: 'Jumbo structures including 5% down, no-MI, and asset depletion qualifying.' },
  { icon: 'truck', title: 'Texas relocations', text: 'Out-of-state buyers moving into Central Texas on a compressed timeline.' },
];

const credentials = [
  { label: 'Licensed mortgage advisor', value: site.nmls, href: site.nmlsLookup },
  { label: 'Institution', value: `${site.institution} · ${site.institutionNmls}`, href: site.institutionNmlsLookup },
  { label: 'Experience', value: '20+ years originating residential mortgages' },
  { label: 'Licensed to serve', value: 'Texas and clients nationwide' },
  { label: 'Based in', value: 'Georgetown, Texas — Williamson County' },
  { label: 'Regulatory standing', value: 'Equal Housing Lender · Member FDIC' },
];

const personSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: site.advisor,
  jobTitle: 'Mortgage Advisor',
  description: `${site.advisor} is a licensed mortgage advisor with more than 20 years of experience, serving Texas and clients nationwide through ${site.institution}.`,
  url: new URL('/about', site.url).toString(),
  image: new URL('/images/jason-headshot-large.webp', site.url).toString(),
  telephone: '+1-760-715-3434',
  email: site.email,
  worksFor: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: site.institution,
  },
  address: {
    '@type': 'PostalAddress',
    addressLocality: site.city,
    addressRegion: site.state,
    addressCountry: 'US',
  },
};

const schema = combineSchema(personSchema, breadcrumbSchema(crumbs));
---

<PageLayout
  title="About Jason Herbert, Mortgage Advisor"
  description="Meet Jason Herbert, a Georgetown, TX mortgage advisor with 20+ years of experience solving financing problems for self-employed buyers, veterans, investors, and first-time homeowners."
  heroEyebrow="About"
  heroTitle="20 Years of Saying “Here’s How We Do It” Instead of “No.”"
  heroSubtitle="I am not the lender with the flashiest rate ad. I am the one people call after somebody else turned them down — and the one smart buyers call first so they never hear no in the first place."
  heroImage="/images/hero/about-hero.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Jason Herbert meeting with clients in Georgetown, Texas"
  crumbs={crumbs}
  schema={schema}
>
  <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------------- my story -->
  <Section bg="white">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.15fr_1fr] lg:gap-16">
      <div>
        <SectionHeading eyebrow="My Story" title="How I Ended Up Doing This" align="left" class="mb-7" />
        <div class="space-y-5 text-body-lg text-graytext">
          <p>
            I did not set out to be a mortgage guy. Like a lot of people in this industry, I found it sideways — and
            then discovered that the part I liked most was the part everyone else seemed to treat as an obstacle. The
            complicated files. The self-employed borrower with fourteen deposits a month. The veteran whose entitlement
            nobody had bothered to calculate correctly. The couple who had been told no somewhere else and had no idea
            why.
          </p>
          <p>
            Twenty years in, I have watched the industry cycle through a housing boom, a collapse, a recovery, a
            historic run of low rates, and a sharp correction back to reality. That cycle teaches you something you
            cannot learn any other way: rates are temporary and structure is permanent. The borrowers who got hurt in
            2008 were not the ones with a quarter point too much on their rate. They were the ones in a product nobody
            had explained to them.
          </p>
          <p>
            So I built my practice around the opposite. I diagnose before I prescribe. I say no to deals that do not
            serve the client. And I explain everything, in plain English, until the person across from me can repeat it
            back.
          </p>
        </div>

        <SectionHeading
          eyebrow="Why “Solution Expert” Is Not a Slogan"
          title="Because a Denial Is Usually Just a Program Gap"
          align="left"
          class="mb-7 mt-12"
        />
        <div class="space-y-5 text-body-lg text-graytext">
          <p>
            Most lenders offer a narrow menu. If your file fits the menu, you get approved. If it does not, you get a
            letter. Nobody at that company is doing anything wrong exactly — they just do not have the tool your
            situation requires, and there is no incentive to tell you that the tool exists elsewhere.
          </p>
          <p>
            I keep a wide menu on purpose. Conventional, FHA, VA, jumbo, construction, DSCR, bank statement, 1099, P&amp;L,
            no-ratio, asset depletion, first-lien HELOC, non-contingent purchase programs. Not because variety is
            impressive, but because the twelfth option is sometimes the one that gets a family into a house.
          </p>
          <p>
            When I say I solve mortgage problems rather than quote rates, that is what I mean. Bring me the situation
            that stumped somebody else. That is genuinely the work I enjoy most.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-28 lg:self-start">
        <img
          src="/images/jason-headshot-large.webp"
          alt={`${site.advisor}, ${site.positioning}`}
          width="1000"
          height="1250"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-card bg-gradient-to-b from-silver-light to-white object-cover shadow-card-hover"
        />
        <div class="mt-6 rounded-card border border-silver-light bg-offwhite p-6">
          <p class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-navy">{site.advisor}</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-graytext">{site.positioning}</p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-graytext">{site.nmls} · {site.institution}</p>
          <div class="mt-5 flex flex-col gap-3">
            <Button href="/schedule" variant="primary" size="sm" icon="arrow-right" fullWidth track="schedule">
              Book a Free Strategy Call
            </Button>
            <Button href={site.phoneHref} variant="secondary" size="sm" fullWidth>
              Call {site.phone}
            </Button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------------- philosophy -->
  <Section bg="offwhite">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="My Philosophy"
      title="Three Commitments I Do Not Compromise On"
      align="center"
      class="mb-12"
    />
    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {
        philosophy.map((item) => (
          <div class="reveal flex h-full flex-col rounded-card border border-silver-light bg-white p-7 shadow-card">
            <span class="inline-flex h-14 w-14 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-brandblue-soft text-brandblue">
              <Icon name={item.icon} size={26} />
            </span>
            <h3 class="mt-5 font-heading text-h3 text-navy">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 flex-1 leading-relaxed text-graytext">{item.text}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------------- who I work with -->
  <Section bg="white">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="Who I Work With"
      title="Eight Situations I See Constantly"
      subtitle="If you recognize yourself in one of these, there is a good chance I have solved your exact problem before."
      align="center"
      class="mb-12"
    />
    <div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
      {
        clients.map((client) => (
          <div class="reveal flex h-full flex-col rounded-card border border-silver-light bg-white p-6 shadow-card transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-card-hover">
            <span class="inline-flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-brandblue-soft text-brandblue">
              <Icon name={client.icon} size={22} />
            </span>
            <h3 class="mt-4 font-heading text-base font-bold text-navy">{client.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-graytext">{client.text}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------------- credentials -->
  <Section bg="navy">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.2fr] lg:gap-16">
      <div>
        <SectionHeading
          eyebrow="Credentials"
          title="Licensed, Regulated, and Bank-Backed"
          align="left"
          invert
          eyebrowColor="gold"
          subtitle="I originate through Primis Mortgage Company, the mortgage arm of Primis Bank. That means a federally regulated, FDIC-insured institution stands behind your loan — a genuine difference from a broker-only shop."
        />
      </div>
      <dl class="overflow-hidden rounded-card border border-white/15 bg-white/5">
        {
          credentials.map((item, index) => (
            <div class:list={['flex flex-col gap-1 px-6 py-5 sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:gap-6', index % 2 === 1 ? 'bg-white/5' : '']}>
              <dt class="font-heading text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-silver sm:w-2/5">
                {item.label}
              </dt>
              <dd class="flex-1 font-medium text-white">
                {item.href ? (
                  <a href={item.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-brandblue">
                    {item.value}
                  </a>
                ) : (
                  item.value
                )}
              </dd>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </dl>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------------- beyond the loan -->
  <Section bg="offwhite">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-16">
      <div>
        <SectionHeading eyebrow="Beyond the Loan" title="Life in Georgetown" align="left" class="mb-7" />
        <div class="space-y-5 text-body-lg text-graytext">
          <p>
            Georgetown is home. It is the kind of place where you run into your clients at the grocery store, which is
            an excellent accountability system for anyone in a service business. I have financed homes for neighbors,
            for their kids, and in a few cases for their parents.
          </p>
          <p>
            Outside of work, most of my time goes to family. I also spend a fair amount of it making mortgage education
            videos, which started as a way to answer the same question once instead of forty times and turned into
            something people actually watch. If you would rather learn from a five-minute video than a phone call, a lot
            of that is already published.
          </p>
          <p>
            The through line, at work and otherwise, is that I would rather be useful than impressive. Twenty years in a
            relationship business will teach you that the two are not the same thing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <Button href={site.social.youtube} variant="secondary" external icon="play" iconPosition="left">
            Watch on YouTube
          </Button>
          <Button href="/contact" variant="tertiary" icon="arrow-right">Get in touch</Button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div
          class="flex aspect-video w-full flex-col items-center justify-center rounded-card border-2 border-dashed border-silver bg-white p-8 text-center"
        >
          <span class="inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brandblue-soft text-brandblue">
            <Icon name="play" size={30} />
          </span>
          <p class="mt-5 font-heading text-lg font-bold text-navy">Video introduction</p>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-sm text-sm text-graytext">
            {/* TODO: Replace with the embedded YouTube introduction video once final footage is available. */}
            A short introduction video will live here. Until then, the YouTube channel has dozens of full-length
            mortgage explainers.
          </p>
          <Button href={site.social.youtube} variant="primary" size="sm" class="mt-5" external icon="arrow-right">
            Visit the channel
          </Button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <TestimonialStrip title="What Clients Say About Working With Me" bg="white" />
</PageLayout>
